<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>In the category field on the request or incident form, it’s possible to only display the level 3 record categories. The following rule will search the level2Parent field and confirms that the value is populated, the level2parent field contains the name of the parent of the 3<sup>rd</sup> level value so it will only be populated if the record is a 3<sup>rd</sup> level category. A dummy value is used for the comparison, in this case, ‘Empty’. The rule will only compare it to valid values; categories with a null in the field will not be displayed in the drop-down list.
</p><p><a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="xc bre ex5 1.png" src="/mediawiki/images/e/e6/xc_bre_ex5_1.png" width="891" height="123" data-file-width="891" data-file-height="123"></a>
</p><p><br> 
</p>
